# Curosr Rules

- Develop TypeScript, Astro, and TailwindCSS applications following provided conventions and guidelines.

## Code Style and Structure\*\*

> > > > > > > multilingual

- Write concise, technical TypeScript code using functional and declarative programming patterns.
- Avoid classes; prefer iteration and modularization over code duplication.
- Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., `isLoading`, `hasError`).
- Structure files into: exported component, subcomponents, helpers, static content, and types.
- don't use any, use type instead.
- don't use abrevations, use the full word instead (e.g. `e` -> `event` )
- colors:
  - dark:
    - background: slate-950 # Fond principal
    - text: zinc-100 # Texte principal
    - textSecondary: zinc-400 # Texte secondaire
    - accent1: amber-500 # Accent 1 (UI)
    - accent2: emerald-400 # Accent 2 (UI)
    - surface: slate-800 # Surfaces
  - light:
    - background: zinc-50 # Fond principal
    - text: zinc-900 # Texte principal
    - textSecondary: zinc-500 # Texte secondaire
    - accent1: amber-600 # Accent 1 (UI)
    - accent2: emerald-600 # Accent 2 (UI)
      surface: zinc-200 # Surfaces

## Naming Conventions\*\*

- Use lowercase with dashes for directories (e.g., `components/auth-wizard`).
- Favor named exports for components.

## TypeScript Usage\*\*

- Use TypeScript for all code; prefer types over interfaces.
- Avoid enums; use maps instead.
- Use functional components with TypeScript types.

## Syntax and Formatting\*\*

> > > > > > > multilingual

- Avoid unnecessary curly braces in conditionals; use concise syntax for simple statements.
- Write declarative JSX.

## UI and Styling

- Use Tailwind for components and styling.
- Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS using a mobile-first approach.
- NEVER use custom CSS classes - use only Tailwind utility classes.

### Button and Icon Guidelines

- All buttons with SVG icons MUST use `flex items-center justify-center` classes.
- For buttons with icon + text, use `flex items-center justify-center gap-2`.
- Pagination buttons MUST use `flex items-center justify-center px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium transition-colors`.
- Never create custom CSS classes for button styling - use Tailwind utilities only.

### Modal System Guidelines

- Use the unified Modal system (`src/components/ui/Modal.astro`) for all new modals.
- Modal components should extend the base Modal with slots: `title`, content, `footer`.
- Use event-driven architecture: emit custom events for modal actions.
- Modal IDs should be descriptive (e.g., `delete-vinyl-modal`, `add-to-collection-modal`).
- Always use `modalManager.openModal(id)` and `modalManager.closeModal(id)` for consistency.
- Avoid creating inline modals with `innerHTML` - use component-based approach.

### Data Handling

- Extract all available vinyl data using utility functions.
- Enrich data with Discogs API when possible, but handle failures gracefully.
- Use optional fields to prevent 404 errors when API data is missing.
- Always validate and sanitize data before sending to APIs.

### Code Organization and Refactoring

- Create utility functions in `src/utils/` for reusable logic.
- Avoid code duplication - extract common patterns into utilities.
- Use centralized exports in `src/utils/index.ts`.
- Prefer composition over inheritance for component logic.
- Extract complex functions from components into separate utility files.
- Use typed utility functions with proper TypeScript interfaces.
- Group related utilities in dedicated files (e.g., `vinyl-data-extractor.ts`, `notification-modals.ts`).

### Error Handling and User Feedback

- Use the unified notification system (`src/utils/notification-modals.ts`) for user feedback.
- Provide loading states with `setButtonLoading()` and `resetButton()` utilities.
- Always handle API failures gracefully with fallback behavior.
- Show informative error messages instead of generic alerts.
- Use proper TypeScript error types and validation.

## Performance Optimization\*\*

> > > > > > > multilingual

- Use dynamic loading for non-critical components.
- Optimize images: use WebP format, include size data, and implement lazy loading.
